id: pm-iqgj
title: "Recover 16 unreadable TOON item files: strict decoder mis-parses bracketed tokens followed by a colon inside quoted text fields"
description: "Root cause: the upstream @toon-format/toon 2.3.0 decoder (latest) has a round-trip bug. parseArrayHeaderLine scans the WHOLE line for an opening bracket when the key is unquoted, so a quoted scalar VALUE that contains a bracketed token immediately followed by a colon (e.g. a redacted endpoint marker, an Unreleased changelog marker, a 'med' severity tag, or a sntr-style pattern) is mis-detected as a 'key[N]:' array header. Because pm calls decode in the library default strict mode, parseBracketSegment then throws 'Invalid array length', and parseToonItemDocument converts that to 'TOON item document is not valid TOON'. The library's own encode() emits exactly this ambiguous (but otherwise correctly double-quoted) form, so it cannot round-trip its own output. Impact: 16 closed item files currently fail to load (item_list_item_read_failed) and are excluded from pm list/get/search and the pm-changelog generator (item_count 782 vs ~820 checked by validate). Confirmed non-strict decode reads all 16 correctly: full body text and comments arrays are preserved, and a valid file parses identically under strict vs non-strict. Fix: parseToonItemDocument tries strict decode first, then falls back to lenient decode on failure (preserving strict duplicate-key protection for normal files), surfaced via onWarning. Add a pure helper + tests."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
