acceptance_criteria: All 16 previously-unreadable items load via pm get/list/search; pm list emits zero item_list_item_read_failed warnings; valid files still parse strictly (duplicate-key protection retained for the non-bracket case); a focused unit test covers a bracketed-token-then-colon body round-trip; pnpm build and coverage gate pass; pm-changelog item_count rises to include recovered closed items.
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-24T06:36:34.360Z",claude-code-agent,"Root cause confirmed and fixed. Added src/core/item/toon-decode.ts with decodeToonItemContent(): try strict decode, fall back to lenient on failure, rethrow strict error if lenient also fails. Wired into parseToonItemDocument (item-format.ts) which now emits onWarning 'toon_item_decoded_with_lenient_fallback' on the fallback path. Verified against freshly-built dist: all 16 previously-unreadable items now load (16/16), pm list emits zero item_list_item_read_failed warnings, and a valid file parses identically under strict vs non-strict (duplicate-key protection retained for normal docs). New module added to vitest include for 100% coverage; item-format.ts is already in both include+exclude (not gated)."
  "2026-05-24T07:00:10.677Z",claude-code-agent,"COORDINATOR VERIFIED 2026-05-24: full coverage gate green (108 files, 1621 tests, 100% stmts/branch/funcs/lines), static-quality-gate passed, typecheck clean, secret-scan clean. Recovery is SILENT (no health-flipping warning) — pm health now ok:true (was ok:false from 16 read failures); pm validate ok:true checked_items 837 (was 820); 16/16 items load. Dogfooded in temp repo: created an item with a bracketed-token-then-colon description, read it back byte-identical, zero read-failed warnings. Downstream pm-changelog generator gap tracked separately as pm-hybj (bundled stale SDK)."
